{"key":"processedPost-17016892","value":{"id":17016892,"first":17015013,"last":17039229,"when":1350044027,"utime":"10/12/12 03:13 PM","content":"<blockquote>Quote:<br /><b>Tmethyl said:</b><br /><br />Any idea why it's pinning on bottom even with NO light? (I know other factors are involved in pinning, but this is crazy)<br /></blockquote><br /><br />It does no good to tape the bottom of a tub because light anywhere on a substrate will trigger pins anywhere else on the substrate where conditions are optimal.&nbsp; The gap around the edges of a shrinking substrate provides the perfect conditions for pinning, and a tub that gets moved after preparation opens up lots of air gaps on the bottom too.<br /><br />Don't dunk tubs for 24 hours.&nbsp; That's for cakes.&nbsp; You shouldn't submerge a large substrate for more than an hour or two or it will over-hydrate.<br />RR","title":"Re: The bottom of the tub..","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}